OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FOfcom: A third of children 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fhave adult social media    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, One in three children lie about their  
OL,6, age to access adult content on social  
OL,7, media, according to research           
OL,8, commissioned by the regulator, Ofcom.  
OL,10,FMany social media sites, such as       
OL,11,FInstagram, do not permit under-13s to  
OL,12,Fsign up, while accounts for under-18s  
OL,13,Fhave limited functionality.            
OL,15,FBut researchers found children were    
OL,16,Ffaking their ages to skirt the rules.  
OL,18,FOfcom says this increases the risk of  
OL,19,Fchildren seeing content which may be   
OL,20,Finappropriate or harmful.              
